---HEADER---
file:                  tooling/propagation.py
language:              python
role:                  Four subcommands managing the .llmpropstts file:
                       prop-start (create cascade), prop-done (mark
                       island complete; auto-deletes file when pending
                       empties), prop-status (read state), prop-finish
                       (delete file; refuses if pending without --force).
layer:                 data
status:                verified
confidence:            high (rationale: authored fresh in rc7, smoke-
                       tested end-to-end with prop-start -> 3x prop-done
                       -> auto-finish -> prop-status -> no-cascade)
generation-pass:       false
read-reason:           task-driven
last-verified:         v0.3-2026-05-07
maintained-by:         llm
exports:
  - PROPSTTS_FILE
  - cmd_prop_start
  - setup_prop_start
  - cmd_prop_done
  - setup_prop_done
  - cmd_prop_status
  - setup_prop_status
  - cmd_prop_finish
  - setup_prop_finish
  - SUBCOMMANDS
imports:
  - argparse
  - datetime                  :: datetime, timezone
  - pathlib                   :: Path
  - tooling.common            :: find_project_root
  - tooling.types             :: Finding, Report
depends-on:
  - llmisland_tooling.py      :: orchestrator iterates SUBCOMMANDS
  - .llmpropstts (runtime)    :: created/read/written/deleted by these
                                  subcommands at the project root
translation-boundary:  none
dynamic-boundary:      false

---SYMBOLS---

SYMBOL: PROPSTTS_FILE
kind:           constant
pure:           true
total:          true
latency-budget: N/A
effects:
  reads:    none
  mutates:  none
  allocs:   none
  throws:   never
  async:    false
  io:       none
called-by:
  - all four cmd_prop_* functions :: filesystem path construction
calls:
  - none
expects:
  - none
runtime-dependencies:
  - none
tests:
  unit:       none — string literal
  regression: none
  security:   none
business-rule: N/A
fragility:    low
fragility-note: N/A

SYMBOL: cmd_prop_start
kind:           function
pure:           false (filesystem write + reads system clock)
total:          true
latency-budget: <100ms
effects:
  reads:    filesystem (existing .llmpropstts), system clock
  mutates:  filesystem (creates .llmpropstts at project root)
  allocs:   data dict + Report
  throws:   never (catches filesystem errors via OS path checks)
  async:    false
  io:       filesystem write
called-by:
  - llmisland_tooling.main :: dispatch on 'prop-start'
calls:
  - find_project_root, _read, _write, datetime.now
expects:
  - args.cascade is a non-empty list of filenames
  - .llmpropstts MUST NOT already exist (refuses to clobber)
runtime-dependencies:
  - none
tests:
  unit:       none yet
  regression: rc7 smoke test passed
  security:   none
business-rule: N/A
fragility:    medium (rationale: clobber prevention is the only safety;
                                  if the existing-check fails, the user
                                  loses an in-progress cascade)
fragility-note: the existing-cascade check is the load-bearing safety
                here. If _read returns None on a malformed but present
                .llmpropstts, prop-start would overwrite it. Acceptable
                for now because manual edits are discouraged (see
                SPEC/07_PROPAGATION.md), but rc8 validate could add a
                check that .llmpropstts has the expected shape.

SYMBOL: cmd_prop_done
kind:           function
pure:           false (filesystem read + write or delete)
total:          true
latency-budget: <50ms
effects:
  reads:    filesystem (.llmpropstts)
  mutates:  filesystem (rewrites .llmpropstts; deletes when pending empty)
  allocs:   data dict + Report
  throws:   never
  async:    false
  io:       filesystem read+write
called-by:
  - llmisland_tooling.main :: dispatch on 'prop-done'
calls:
  - find_project_root, _read, _write, _normalize_island, Path.unlink
expects:
  - args.island is a string (with or without .llmisland suffix)
  - .llmpropstts exists (returns no-cascade error otherwise)
runtime-dependencies:
  - none
tests:
  unit:       none yet
  regression: rc7 smoke test: completing the last pending island
              correctly auto-deletes .llmpropstts
  security:   none
business-rule: N/A
fragility:    medium (rationale: auto-delete on empty pending is the
                                  trickiest path; a future change that
                                  breaks it leaves orphan .llmpropstts
                                  files in projects)
fragility-note: rc8 validate.py should add a check for .llmpropstts
                with empty pending — that is an inconsistent state
                that prop-done is supposed to prevent.

SYMBOL: cmd_prop_status
kind:           function
pure:           false (filesystem read)
total:          true
latency-budget: <50ms
effects:
  reads:    filesystem (.llmpropstts)
  mutates:  none
  allocs:   data dict + Report
  throws:   never
  async:    false
  io:       filesystem read
called-by:
  - llmisland_tooling.main :: dispatch on 'prop-status'
calls:
  - find_project_root, _read
expects:
  - .llmpropstts exists OR is missing (both are valid states)
runtime-dependencies:
  - none
tests:
  unit:       none yet
  regression: rc7 smoke test: reports cascade_open: false when missing
              and cascade_open: true with full state when present
  security:   none
business-rule: N/A
fragility:    low
fragility-note: N/A

SYMBOL: cmd_prop_finish
kind:           function
pure:           false (filesystem read + delete)
total:          true
latency-budget: <50ms
effects:
  reads:    filesystem (.llmpropstts)
  mutates:  filesystem (deletes .llmpropstts)
  allocs:   data dict + Report
  throws:   never
  async:    false
  io:       filesystem read+delete
called-by:
  - llmisland_tooling.main :: dispatch on 'prop-finish'
calls:
  - find_project_root, _read, Path.unlink
expects:
  - args.force is bool
  - .llmpropstts exists OR is missing (both are valid states)
runtime-dependencies:
  - none
tests:
  unit:       none yet
  regression: rc7 smoke test: refuses without --force when pending
              remain; force-deletes with abandoned-pending warning
  security:   none
business-rule: N/A
fragility:    low
fragility-note: N/A

SYMBOL: SETUP_FAMILY
kind:           function
pure:           true (each mutates only the parser passed in)
total:          true
latency-budget: <1ms each
effects:
  reads:    none
  mutates:  argparse.ArgumentParser passed in
  allocs:   none meaningful
  throws:   never
  async:    false
  io:       none
called-by:
  - llmisland_tooling.build_parser :: at parser construction, once each
calls:
  - parser.add_argument (setup_prop_status adds nothing — no flags)
expects:
  - parser supports add_argument
runtime-dependencies:
  - none
tests:
  unit:       none yet
  regression: none yet
  security:   none
business-rule: N/A
fragility:    low
fragility-note: this is one representative entry covering setup_prop_start,
                setup_prop_done, setup_prop_status, setup_prop_finish.
                All four have the trivial parser-config shape; treating
                them as a family avoids 4 near-identical SYMBOL entries.
                If any one's behavior diverges, give it its own SYMBOL
                entry (HD-004 in tooling/validate.py.llmisland documents
                the same pattern for the ENUM family there).

SYMBOL: SUBCOMMANDS
kind:           constant
pure:           true
total:          true
latency-budget: N/A
effects:
  reads:    none
  mutates:  none
  allocs:   one dict at import time
  throws:   never
  async:    false
  io:       none
called-by:
  - llmisland_tooling.build_parser :: iterates module.SUBCOMMANDS
calls:
  - none
expects:
  - keys: prop-start, prop-done, prop-status, prop-finish
  - values: (setup_fn, handler_fn, helptext) tuples
runtime-dependencies:
  - none
tests:
  unit:       none yet
  regression: none yet
  security:   none
business-rule: N/A
fragility:    low
fragility-note: N/A

---RISKS---

security:                none
regression-sensitivity:
  - changes to the .llmpropstts on-disk format break every command in
    this module and break manual fallback documented in SPEC/07
  - prop-start's clobber-prevention is load-bearing; a regression
    there can lose an in-progress cascade
platform-sensitivity:
  - filesystem case sensitivity differs between Windows and POSIX;
    .llmpropstts is one fixed name so this does not matter in
    practice
  - datetime.now(timezone.utc) is portable but the displayed format
    is ISO 8601 with seconds, no fractional seconds
config-dependencies: none

---MEMORY---

ACTIVE-CONSTRAINTS:
  - id: AC-001
    constraint:  the on-disk format of .llmpropstts is fixed
                 (status / started / origin / pending / completed).
                 Any change breaks SPEC/07_PROPAGATION.md's documented
                 manual fallback and is a Tier C change.
    established: 2026-05-05
    evidence:    SPEC/07_PROPAGATION.md PROPAGATION STATE FILE section

  - id: AC-002
    constraint:  prop-start MUST refuse to clobber an existing
                 .llmpropstts. Force-overriding it would silently
                 destroy an in-progress cascade.
    established: 2026-05-05
    evidence:    inferred-from-design (HD-001)

  - id: AC-003
    constraint:  prop-done MUST auto-delete .llmpropstts when the
                 last pending island is marked done. The presence
                 of the file is itself the signal that a cascade
                 is in progress; leaving an empty-pending file is
                 an inconsistent state.
    established: 2026-05-05
    evidence:    SPEC/07_PROPAGATION.md cascade protocol step e

HISTORICAL-DECISIONS:
  - id: HD-001
    decision:  prop-start refuses clobber even with no flag override
    reason:    the user has prop-finish --force for cleanup; there
               is no scenario where clobbering an existing cascade
               is the right action without explicit user intent.
               Refusing to overwrite forces the user through finish.
    date:      2026-05-05
    outcome:   stable
    evidence:  inferred-from-design

  - id: HD-002
    decision:  auto-delete on prop-done when pending becomes empty
    reason:    SPEC/07_PROPAGATION.md says "delete .llmpropstts when
               all pending entries are resolved" — the file's
               presence IS the cascade-open signal. Auto-delete keeps
               that signal honest without requiring the user to
               remember to call prop-finish.
    date:      2026-05-05
    outcome:   stable
    evidence:  SPEC/07_PROPAGATION.md

  - id: HD-003
    decision:  islands list uses "  - none" when empty, not omission
    reason:    the SPEC/07_PROPAGATION.md format example always
               shows pending and completed lists; making the file
               structurally consistent across states means manual
               readers see the same shape every time.
    date:      2026-05-05
    outcome:   stable
    evidence:  SPEC/07_PROPAGATION.md format example

SUPERSEDED:
  - none yet
